//✅ 1.Basic Traversal & Observations
//Check if the array is sorted

//PROBLEM STATEMENT---

/*

Problem Statement
You are given an array nums of size N. Determine whether the given array is a non-decreasing sorted array that has been rotated any number of times (including zero).
An array is considered sorted and rotated if:
There exists a non-decreasing sorted array A.
After rotating 
A by some k positions (k ≥ 0)
(k≥0), we obtain the given array nums.
Duplicates are allowed in the array.

What is Rotation?
Rotation means moving a suffix of the array to the front while maintaining the order of elements.
Example:
Original Sorted Array
1 2 3 4 5
After rotating by 4 positions
2 3 4 5 1
Both arrays represent a sorted and rotated array.

Mathematical Definition
If A is the original sorted array and it is rotated right by k positions, the resulting array B satisfies:
B[(i + k) mod A.length] = A[i]
for every valid index i.

Function Declaration

Function Name
check

Description
This function checks whether a given array nums is a non-decreasing sorted array that has been rotated any number of times (including zero rotations).
Parameters
nums : reference to a vector/array of integers
Represents the given array.
Return Value
The function should return:
true  → if nums can be obtained by rotating a non-decreasing sorted array
false → otherwise

Constraints
1 ≤ nums.length ≤ 100
1 ≤ nums[i] ≤ 100

Input Format
The first line contains an integer T — number of test cases.
For each test case:
The first line contains an integer N — size of the array.
The second line contains N space-separated integers — elements of the array nums.

Output Format
For each test case, print:
true
if the array is sorted and rotated, otherwise print
false
Each result should be printed on a new line.

Sample Test Cases

Sample 1
Input
1
7
6 7 1 2 3 4 5

Output
true

Explanation
Original sorted array:
1 2 3 4 5 6 7
After rotating by k = 2 positions
6 7 1 2 3 4 5
Hence the array is sorted and rotated.

Sample 2

Input
1
5
68 97 10 21 45

Output
true

Explanation
Original sorted array:
10 21 45 68 97
After rotating by k = 2
68 97 10 21 45
Hence the array is sorted and rotated.

Sample 3

Input
1
5
4 5 2 3 1

Output
false

Explanation
No rotation of any sorted array can produce the order:
4 5 2 3 1
Therefore, the array is not sorted and rotated.


*/


//SOLUTION----

/*

  public static boolean check(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int breakCount = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
            if (nums[i] > nums[i + 1]) {
                breakCount++;
            }
        }
        if (nums[n - 1] > nums[0]) {
            breakCount++;
        }
        return breakCount <= 1;
    }

